Along with others as well.

I've personally never been a real fan of using Eclipse for OCaml developmen=
t.  I feel like the good reasons to use Eclipse are for languages with huge=
 overhead in naming conventions and boilerplate, Java being the case in poi=
nt example.  By contrast, in OCaml most people use the module system and I'=
ve usually been able to get by with swapping between a few buffers of inter=
face files.  Of course, YMMV.

